   <body>
      <p>The conveyor belt is tensioned and guided via the tensioning station. The tensioning pulley</p>
      <p>(1) is moved in a straight line via tensioning spindles (2), thereby increasing or reducing the tension of the conveyor belt. The tensioning pulley is mounted on two pedestal bearings (4) by means of a shaft (3) and is able to rotate. A rotary survey is mounted at the end of the shaft (5).</p>
